## 1. Purpose

This policy establishes the end-to-end process for requesting, evaluating, approving, onboarding, and decommissioning AI tools and services at {{ business_name }}. It ensures that AI procurement decisions account for privacy obligations under the **Privacy Act 1988**, transparency requirements under the **POLA Act 2024**, and governance expectations from the **AI6 Guidance for AI Adoption** (October 2024).

---

## 2. Scope

This policy applies to:

- Purchase or subscription to any AI-powered software, platform, or API
- Free-tier or trial usage of AI tools that process organisational or personal data
- Open-source AI models deployed on {{ business_name }}'s infrastructure
- AI features embedded in existing software (e.g., AI assistants in productivity suites)
- AI tools used by contractors or third parties on {{ business_name }}'s behalf

{% if shadow_ai_controls %}
{{ business_name }} has shadow AI controls in place. Any AI tool adoption that bypasses this process will be treated as a shadow AI incident and escalated under the AI Acceptable Use Policy.
{% else %}
**Shadow AI note:** Using AI tools without following this procurement process constitutes Shadow AI and is governed by the {{ business_name }} AI Acceptable Use Policy. {{ business_name }} does not currently have technical shadow AI controls — implementing this process is a critical first step.
{% endif %}

